The paper discusses an algorithm that optimally distributes resources between the execution of provably correct programs and an enumeration of all proofs, including relevant proofs of program correctness and of time bounds on program runtimes. This suggests that the paper may belong to the categories of computational complexity (cs.CC), information theory (cs.IT), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), and machine learning (cs.LG).
